Articles.Content: @nightingale: I did try uninstalling Strategia, and it didn't change much.  I did see more of the Admin Building screen for longer periods of time, but with the mouse in certain spots, the view still switched to KSC.  I can't discern a pattern to why or when screens change; certain spots seem to trigger the change, but those spots don't correlate with any of the various images in the Admin Building.  I'll uninstall the environmental mods next to see if they're the problem.  It's slow going; loading the game takes me a few minutes, and I have only so much patience.  I have no idea how you modders test stuff without going insane.

First off - love the idea of the mod. Just started a new career, and I'm looking forward to trying these strategies out.

I have a very similar issue to Mister Spock, but with the R&D building - when I click on it, it flashes up for a brief second, then the KSC comes back. I noticed that the log pops up a message repeatedly that says "No RDNode registered with id !" It occurs at exactly the moment I click on the R&D building. Didn't seem to be associated with any exceptions in the log though.

I'm not sure if it's got anything to do with Strategia at all, but this was after the first flight since I activated the Local Science I strategy, so I thought I'd have a look here to see if it was a known issue. I'm only commenting now as Mister Spock has a very similar problem.

I've also got a fairly extensive mod list (loading takes about 6 mins), so I'll do some checking with a more minimal install tomorrow.

Log's here, if you want to take a look. There's a fair few exceptions from other mods, though. I noticed loads from KRASH, and also some from CactEye, KAC, EVE and MechJeb. Like I say, I'll do some testing with a more minimal install tomorrow.

--Update: I can't reproduce the problem anymore. I still get the "No RDNode" message, but it seems to work fine now. The only changes I've made are to remove CactEye and TST. Apologies for impugning the good name of your fine mod.

Edited May 19, 2016 by UnanimousCoward

Wow. Thanks.

@nightingale Just FYI, I still can't use your mod -- or, for that matter, the stock Admin Building.  I've uninstalled your mod, EVE, Stock Visual Enhancements, and several other mods.  When I enter the Admin Building, the screen flickers between Admin Building and KSC depending on where my mouse cursor is.  Remaining mod list:  Historic Missions Contract Pack, severedsolo's Bases & Stations, Achievements, Aviation Lights, BahaSP, CRP, EVE, Firespitter, Indicator Lights, KER, Planetary Base Systems, PreciseNode, RasterProp, Raidernick's two probe packs, SCANSat, scatterer, Smoke Screen, Station Science, TextureReplacer, and KAC.  I guess I'll try removing Smoke Screen and scatterer next.

Not asking for any support -- just thought I'd keep you informed, since you obviously have an interest in people being able to use the Admin Building.  I seem to be the only user with this issue, and it's not specific to your mod, as I can't use the stock Admin Building either.  I'll poke around to see if I can learn more.  And I'll keep uninstalling stuff as much as my patience allows.  I actually never use the stock Admin system, so it's not game-breaking for me, but I was looking forward to trying Strategia.  We'll see.

More of an predictable peculiarity than a bug; when you are running a modded Kerbin with no moons, most of the first two columns of strategies do not work. Surprisingly, they DO work properly when Kerbin is a moon of Jool.

More of an predictable peculiarity than a bug; when you are running a modded Kerbin with no moons, most of the first two columns of strategies do not work. Surprisingly, they DO work properly when Kerbin is a moon of Jool.

New Horizons is a fairly common planet mod, so I specifically catered for that situation.  I wasn't aware of any mods where there were no moons though, so I never considered that.  I'll take a look at at that for the next release.
